On Ubuntu 24.04, the recommended way to install the AWS CLI is to download it directly from Amazon.

Here is how to install it properly on your system:

Step 1: Install Dependencies
You need curl and unzip to download and install the CLI.

apt update
apt install -y curl unzip
apt install zip -y

Step 2: Download and Install AWS CLI v2
Run the following commands to download the official installer from Amazon and install it:

cd /tmp
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install

Step 3: Verify Installation
Check that the installation was successful:

aws --version

You should see output similar to: aws-cli/2.x.x Python/3.x.x Linux/5.x.x...

Step 4: Clean up and Configure
You can remove the installation files and then configure your credentials:

Step 4: Clean up and Configure
You can remove the installation files and then configure your credentials:

rm -rf /tmp/aws /tmp/awscliv2.zip
aws configure

It will ask for:

AWS Access Key ID [None]:
AWS Secret Access Key [None]:
Default region name [None]: (e.g., us-east-1 or ap-south-1)ap-south-1
Default output format [None]: (just press Enter to leave blank/json)




